      <i>A Clothing History</i>
      .Extraction of fabrics and waving textiles were first started in the
      Middle East during the late Stone Age. Wearing fabric clothes began from
      100,000 to 500,000 years ago. Knitting was first introduced as a fabric
      creation technique, dating 6500 BC, which is even popular in today's
      fabrics.
    </p>


